4.1 Competitions are open to legal residents of the United Kingdom only, who are aged 18 years or over at the time of entry.

4.2 The following individuals are NOT eligible to enter any Competition:
Employees, directors, officers, agents, or contractors of Golden Dream Draw;
Members of the immediate family (spouse, parent, child, sibling) or household of any person described above;
Any person who has been disqualified from previous competitions operated by the Company;
Any person who is under 18 years of age;
Any person residing outside of the United Kingdom.

4.3 By entering a Competition, you confirm that you satisfy all eligibility requirements. The Company reserves the right to verify eligibility at any stage and to disqualify any entry that does not meet these requirements.

5.1 To enter a Competition via a paid ticket, participants must first hold a registered account with Golden Dream Draw. Account registration requires the successful completion of the Skill Question, as set out in Section 6. Once a valid account is held, participants may purchase tickets as follows:
Visit the official Golden Dream Draw website;
Select the Competition they wish to enter;
Choose the number of tickets they wish to purchase (subject to per-Competition limits);
Confirm their registered account details at checkout;
Complete the checkout process and make payment in full.

5.2 A Competition entry (ticket) is only valid upon receipt of full payment by a participant who holds a valid registered account. Account registration is contingent upon the correct completion of the Skill Question (see Section 6). Entries made by unregistered individuals or accounts created with an incorrect Skill Question answer will be deemed invalid and will not be entered into the Draw.

5.3 Entries are non-transferable. Tickets may not be resold, gifted, or transferred to another person once purchased.

5.4 There is no limit to the number of tickets a participant may purchase per Competition unless stated otherwise on the Competition page. Maximum ticket limits, where applied, will be clearly displayed.

5.5 All entries must be received by the Closing Date as advertised. Entries received after the Closing Date will be void and any payment made will be refunded in accordance with Section 10 of these Terms.

10.1 Under the Consumer Contracts Regulations 2013, you have a right of cancellation in respect of online purchases. However, because Competition entries are time-limited, your right to cancel expires at the earlier of: (a) 14 days from purchase, or (b) the Closing Date of the Competition.

10.2 To request a refund before the Closing Date, contact us at contact@goldendreamdraw.uk with your order reference number. Refund requests will be processed within 5 working days.

10.3 Refunds will NOT be issued in the following circumstances:
After the Closing Date of the Competition has passed;
Where the participant's account was created using an incorrect Skill Question answer and tickets were purchased despite this (e.g. through fraudulent misrepresentation of eligibility);
Where the participant has already been announced as a winner;
Where the refund request is made more than 14 days after purchase.

10.4 If a Competition is cancelled or voided by the Company for any reason, all valid paid entries will be refunded in full within 14 calendar days.

10.5 Refunds will be made to the original payment method used at the time of purchase.

12.1 The Company reserves the right to disqualify any participant who:
Provides false, inaccurate, or misleading information at the point of entry;
Is found to have entered on behalf of another person without authorisation;
Attempts to manipulate the Draw, the selection process, or the operation of any Competition;
Uses automated or mechanical entry methods;
Acts in a manner that is abusive, threatening, or offensive towards Company staff or other participants;
Breaches any provision of these Terms and Conditions.

12.2 In the event of disqualification, no refund will be issued.

13.1 In order to ensure that Golden Dream Draw competitions remain compliant with applicable UK law, a free method of entry is available for every Competition, as follows.

13.2 To submit a free entry by post, the participant must:
Write their full name, date of birth, home address (UK addresses only), email address, telephone number, and the name or reference number of the Competition they wish to enter, on a plain piece of paper (minimum A5 size);
Provide a correct written answer to the Skill Question for that Competition;
Post the completed entry in a stamped envelope to: Golden Dream Draw, PO Box 483, Green Lanes, London, N13 4FG;
Ensure the entry is received at the above address on or before the Closing Date of the relevant Competition.

13.3 In order for a free postal entry to be deemed valid, ALL of the following conditions must be satisfied:
The entry must be handwritten. Printed, typed, or computer-generated entries will not be accepted;
Only one free postal entry is permitted per person, per Competition;
The envelope must be stamped with a valid Royal Mail postage stamp. Franked mail and freepost envelopes will not be accepted;
The entry must be received (not merely postmarked) by the Closing Date;
The correct answer to the Skill Question must be provided and must match the answer published by the Company;
The participant must satisfy all general eligibility requirements set out in Section 4 of these Terms.

13.4 Free postal entries that fail to meet any of the above conditions will be deemed invalid and will not be entered into the Draw.

13.5 Free postal entries carry the same weight and chance of winning as paid entries and will be entered into the same Draw.

13.6 The Company does not accept responsibility for postal entries lost, delayed, or damaged in the mail. It is strongly recommended that participants retain proof of postage.

13.7 The cost of postage for free postal entries is the sole responsibility of the participant.

14.1 Golden Dream Draw is committed to protecting your personal data. We process personal data in accordance with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.

14.2 Personal data collected at the point of entry will be used for the following purposes:
To process your entry and, if applicable, to contact you if you are selected as a winner;
To send you competition-related correspondence;
To comply with our legal obligations;
To prevent fraud and ensure the integrity of our competitions.

14.3 We will not sell, rent, or share your personal data with any third party for marketing purposes without your explicit consent.

14.4 You have the right to access, correct, or request deletion of your personal data at any time. To exercise these rights, contact us at contact@goldendreamdraw.uk.

14.5 Full details of how we handle your personal data are set out in our Privacy Policy, available on our website.

16.1 The Company shall not be liable for any loss or damage suffered by a participant arising from:
Technical failures, server errors, or interruptions to our website or systems;
Entries that are lost, delayed, or corrupted in transit (whether electronic or postal);
Third-party delivery failures once a prize has been dispatched;
Any circumstances outside the Company's reasonable control.

16.2 Nothing in these Terms shall limit or exclude our liability for death or personal injury caused by our negligence, or for fraud or fraudulent misrepresentation.

16.3 To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Company's total liability to any participant shall not exceed the price paid by that participant for their ticket(s) in the relevant Competition.
